<section class="dropdown">
  <h3 id="retrieve-user-profile">6. Retrieve User Profile</h3>

  <p>This endpoint should:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>require a valid API key for a given user in order to succeed (you can decide how the client should send the key in the request, just make sure your documentation indicates the preferred method, i.e. in query paramters, in a request body, in a header, etc.)</li>
    <li>render a JSON representation of users‚Äôs basic attributes as well as the viewing parties they are hosting and attending</li>
    <li>require the user ID for the given user in the path</li>
    <li>return an empty collection of viewing parties if the given user has not hosted or been invited to any parties.</li>
    <li>NOT include any sensitive data in the response, such as the password digest or API key.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Example JSON response for the a user‚Äôs full profile:</p>

  <div class="language-json highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="p">{</span><span class="w">
